1
02:44:57,959 --> 02:44:59,040
[WHISPERING] Hello?

2
02:45:04,719 --> 02:45:05,800
[KNOCKS ECHOING]

3
02:45:14,319 --> 02:45:15,730
[CLEARS THROAT]

4
02:45:18,079 --> 02:45:19,754
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
He's not at home.

5
02:45:20,439 --> 02:45:22,123
Not at home. Ahem.

6
02:45:22,959 --> 02:45:24,040
Good.

7
02:45:25,839 --> 02:45:27,568
Good, good, good.

8
02:46:22,421 --> 02:46:23,436
What's that?

9
02:46:26,439 --> 02:46:28,407
Shush. Shush.

10
02:46:29,719 --> 02:46:31,005
Arkenstone.

11
02:46:32,039 --> 02:46:33,450
Arkenstone.

12
02:46:34,279 --> 02:46:36,327
A large, white jewel.

13
02:46:38,519 --> 02:46:39,884
Very helpful.

14
02:47:18,039 --> 02:47:19,529
[SMAUG EXHALES]

15
02:48:55,399 --> 02:48:57,163
[SNIFFING]

16
02:49:05,861 --> 02:49:07,272
Well...

17
02:49:08,559 --> 02:49:09,845
...thief.

18
02:49:11,839 --> 02:49:15,480
I smell you.

19
02:49:15,839 --> 02:49:19,048
I hear your breath.

20
02:49:20,664 --> 02:49:24,614
I feel your air.

21
02:49:27,454 --> 02:49:29,980
Where are you?

22
02:49:31,453 --> 02:49:32,787
<i>Where are you?</i>

23
02:49:52,645 --> 02:49:56,167
Come now, don't be shy.

24
02:49:56,775 --> 02:49:58,982
Step into the light.

25
02:50:03,550 --> 02:50:04,550
Hmm.

26
02:50:05,988 --> 02:50:09,197
There is something about you.

27
02:50:12,534 --> 02:50:14,416
Something you carry.

28
02:50:15,199 --> 02:50:18,089
Something made of gold.

29
02:50:18,839 --> 02:50:21,681
But far more...

30
02:50:21,882 --> 02:50:23,808
...precious.

31
02:50:24,039 --> 02:50:26,360
VOICE OF THE RING:
<i>Precious! Precious!</i>

32
02:50:29,159 --> 02:50:34,202
There you are,
Thief in the Shadows.

33
02:50:36,039 --> 02:50:38,645
I did not come to steal from you...

34
02:50:39,109 --> 02:50:42,370
...O Smaug the Unassessably Wealthy.

35
02:50:42,902 --> 02:50:45,300
I merely wanted to gaze
upon your magnificence.

36
02:50:45,859 --> 02:50:49,598
To see if you really were
as great as the old tales say.

37
02:50:50,159 --> 02:50:51,888
[WHIMPERS] I did not believe them.

38
02:51:00,719 --> 02:51:04,644
And do you now?!

39
02:51:05,999 --> 02:51:07,249
Truly...

40
02:51:08,559 --> 02:51:10,766
...the tales and songs...

41
02:51:12,321 --> 02:51:17,746
...fall utterly short of your enormity
O Smaug the Stupendous.

42
02:51:18,039 --> 02:51:20,929
Do you think flattery will keep you alive?

43
02:51:21,439 --> 02:51:22,406
No, no.

44
02:51:22,639 --> 02:51:24,129
No, indeed.

45
02:51:26,399 --> 02:51:29,642
You seem familiar with my name...

46
02:51:29,879 --> 02:51:32,769
...but I don't remember smelling
your kind before.

47
02:51:34,308 --> 02:51:38,245
Who are you, and where do you come from...

48
02:51:38,707 --> 02:51:40,800
...may I ask?

49
02:51:50,359 --> 02:51:52,043
I come from under the hill.

50
02:51:52,672 --> 02:51:54,083
Underhill?

51
02:51:57,519 --> 02:52:00,641
BILBO: And under hills and
over hills my path has led.

52
02:52:01,519 --> 02:52:02,361
And... And...

53
02:52:03,119 --> 02:52:05,486
...through the air.
I am he who walks unseen.

54
02:52:05,719 --> 02:52:07,448
Impressive.

55
02:52:08,030 --> 02:52:10,732
What else do you claim to be?

56
02:52:11,100 --> 02:52:12,363
I--I am...

57
02:52:14,719 --> 02:52:16,209
Luck-wearer.

58
02:52:17,833 --> 02:52:19,083
Riddle-maker.

59
02:52:19,391 --> 02:52:21,041
Lovely titles.

60
02:52:21,735 --> 02:52:22,985
<i>Go on.</i>

61
02:52:23,186 --> 02:52:24,311
Barrel-rider.

62
02:52:24,511 --> 02:52:27,913
Barrels? Now that is interesting.

63
02:52:29,534 --> 02:52:33,009
And what about your little Dwarf friends?

64
02:52:34,392 --> 02:52:36,709
Where are they hiding?

65
02:52:38,239 --> 02:52:39,809
Dwarves?

66
02:52:40,639 --> 02:52:41,889
No.

67
02:52:42,601 --> 02:52:45,442
No, no. No Dwarves here.
You've got that all wrong.

68
02:52:45,821 --> 02:52:49,285
Oh, I don't think so, Barrel-rider!

69
02:52:50,057 --> 02:52:53,054
They sent you in here
to do their dirty work...

70
02:52:53,335 --> 02:52:56,090
...while they skulk about outside.

71
02:52:56,759 --> 02:52:58,009
Truly...

72
02:52:58,719 --> 02:53:03,642
...you are mistaken, O Smaug,
Chiefest and Greatest of Calamities.

73
02:53:03,884 --> 02:53:06,801
You have nice manners...

74
02:53:07,374 --> 02:53:08,722
...for a thief...

75
02:53:09,080 --> 02:53:10,588
...and a liar!

76
02:53:11,519 --> 02:53:14,921
I know the smell and taste of Dwarf.

77
02:53:15,788 --> 02:53:17,616
<i>No one better!</i>

78
02:53:18,279 --> 02:53:19,690
It is the gold!

79
02:53:20,155 --> 02:53:24,472
They are drawn to treasure
like flies to dead flesh.

80
02:53:27,694 --> 02:53:30,489
Did you think I did not
know this day would come?!

81
02:53:32,791 --> 02:53:37,760
That a pack of canting Dwarves
would come crawling back...

82
02:53:38,319 --> 02:53:39,651
...to the mountain?!

